
Overview of noun absence

The noun absence has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (25) absence -- (the state of being absent; "he was surprised by the absence of any explanation")
2. (8) absence -- (failure to be present)
3. absence -- (the time interval during which something or somebody is away; "he visited during my absence")
4. absence, absence seizure -- (the occurrence of an abrupt, transient loss or impairment of consciousness (which is not subsequently remembered), sometimes with light twitching, fluttering eyelids, etc.; common in petit mal epilepsy)
